    <cas:Sofa xmi:id="1" sofaNum="1" sofaID="_InitialView" mimeType="text" sofaString="As a result of these interventions, access to education by migrant children has improved since 2018, when the TLC provided the only access,21 and since mid-2019 when 90 per cent of parents with school-age children indicated that their children did not have access to formal education.22 At the end of 2019, over 1,300 children were pursuing their education at CFS (around 600 in those operated by LWC),23 representing around 70 per cent of school-age migrant children. In addition, 771 migrant children had been granted student permits by the Ministry of National Security in 2019, enabling them to be enrolled in state schools.24 While it is not possible to estimate how many of these were actually enrolled,25 it is apparent that a majority of migrant children were attending CFS or other schools prior to the school closures forced by COVID-19 in March 2020"/>
    <cas:View sofa="1" members="8 19 24 29 42 55 68 81 94 107 120 133 146 159 172 185 198 211 224 237 250 263 276 289 302 315 328 341 354 367 380 393 406 419 432 445 458 471 484 497 510 523 536 549 562 575 588 601 614 627 640 653 666 679 692 705 718 731 744 757 770 783 796 809 822 835 848 861 874 887 900 913 926 939 952 965 978 991 1004 1017 1030 1043 1056 1069 1082 1095 1108 1121 1134 1147 1160 1173 1186 1199 1212 1225 1238 1251 1264 1277 1290 1303 1316 1329 1342 1355 1368 1381 1394 1407 1420 1433 1446 1459 1472 1485 1498 1511 1524 1537 1550 1563 1576 1589 1602 1615 1628 1641 1654 1667 1680 1693 1706 1719 1732 1745 1758 1771 1784 1797 1810 1823 1836 1849 1862 1875 1888 1901 1914 1927 1940 1953 1966 1979 1992 2005 2018 2031 2044 2057 2070 2083 2096 2109 2122 2135 2140 2152 2164 2169 2198 2181 2186 2210 2215 2227 2232 2237 2145 2157 2174 2203 2191 2220 2242 2249 2263 2256 2259 2266 2270 2283"/>
